---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Animations"
  description="Index of interactive thermoacoustic-mechanism animations: standing-wave engines and refrigerators; traveling-wave Stirling thermoacoustic engine (in progress)."
>
  <section class="py-8">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-brand-500">
      Research / Animations
    </p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-900">
      Thermoacoustic Mechanism Animations
    </h1>
    <div class="mt-3 h-1 w-16 bg-accent-500" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
      The thermoacoustic effect emerges from coupling between the oscillation
      of gas parcels in a temperature gradient and the heat exchange between
      the parcels and the surrounding wall. We build interactive animations
      contrasting the two canonical regimes — <strong>standing-wave</strong>
      and <strong>traveling-wave</strong> — to help readers see how gas parcels
      cycle under different acoustic configurations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
    <a
      href="/en/research/animations/sdof-vibration"
      class="block rounded-lg border border-brand-100 p-6 transition hover:border-brand-800 hover:shadow-md"
    >
      <p>
        <span
          class="rounded bg-brand-100 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-brand-700"
        >
          Primer ①
        </span>
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-900">Single-DOF Mechanical Vibration</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-brand-500">單自由度機械振動 · first rung</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700">
        The simplest oscillation — a mass on a spring. It builds the phasor
        (complex representation), the <i>90°</i> lead of velocity over
        displacement, the damped decaying spiral, and driven resonance with the
        phase lag — the mechanical prototype for gas-column waves and the
        thermoacoustic mechanism.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-accent-600">Open animation →</p>
    </a>

    <a
      href="/en/research/animations/air-column"
      class="block rounded-lg border border-brand-100 p-6 transition hover:border-brand-800 hover:shadow-md"
    >
      <p>
        <span
          class="rounded bg-brand-100 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-brand-700"
        >
          Primer ②
        </span>
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-900">Standing &amp; Traveling Waves</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-brand-500">氣柱中的駐波與行波 · acoustics primer</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700">
        The acoustics groundwork for the thermoacoustic mechanism: longitudinal
        parcel oscillation forming compressions/rarefactions, traveling vs
        standing waves, nodes/antinodes, boundaries and harmonics, and the
        <i>p</i>–<i>u</i> phase that separates traveling- and standing-wave engines.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-accent-600">Open animation →</p>
    </a>

    <a
      href="/en/research/animations/standing-wave"
      class="block rounded-lg border border-brand-100 p-6 transition hover:border-brand-800 hover:shadow-md"
    >
      <p>
        <span
          class="rounded bg-accent-50 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-accent-700"
        >
          Live
        </span>
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-900">Standing-Wave</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-brand-500">駐波型</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700">
        Synchronized gas-parcel oscillation, P–V trajectory, T–x trajectory, and
        3D orbit. Switch between three wall-temperature gradient regimes
        (uniform, refrigerator, engine) to see the device transition from
        inert, to refrigerator, to engine.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-accent-600">Open animation →</p>
    </a>

    <a
      href="/en/research/animations/traveling-wave"
      class="block rounded-lg border border-brand-100 p-6 transition hover:border-brand-800 hover:shadow-md"
    >
      <p>
        <span
          class="rounded bg-accent-50 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-accent-700"
        >
          New
        </span>
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-900">Traveling-Wave</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-brand-500">行波型 · TASHE</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700">
        The traveling-wave Stirling thermoacoustic engine (TASHE): loop
        topology, the isothermal Stirling cycle in the regenerator,
        <i>p</i>–<i>u</i> in phase, and the energy flow diagram (work flow /
        heat flow). Toggle between a <strong>mechanical α-Stirling engine</strong>
        and the <strong>acoustic loop</strong> — a traveling wave is a
        pistonless Stirling engine.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-accent-600">Open animation →</p>
    </a>
  </section>

  <p class="mt-12 text-sm text-gray-500">
    ← <a href="/en/research/thermoacoustic-effect" class="underline hover:text-accent-600">Back to The Thermoacoustic Effect</a>
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
